oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: H.C. Reynolds
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Mr. & Mrs. H.C. Reynolds and their little daughter, Corley, enthusiastically planting their early spring garden. Mrs. Reynolds is dropping peas and Mr. Reynolds is covering them with a hoe.
Mr. Reynolds owned 65 acres of land.
